external_knowledge:
- A company with a less than perfect track record means its compliance rate is below 100%.;
- Compliance scores are calculated as the ratio of compliant audits to the total number of audits.;
- Companies with a compliance rate of 1 are considered to have a perfect track record. Any rate below this indicates some audits did not meet compliance standards.;

sql:
SELECT company_name
FROM companies
WHERE date(next_audit_date) = date('now', '+30 days');

SELECT company_name
FROM companies
WHERE status <> 'Active' AND company_id NOT IN (
  SELECT DISTINCT company_id 
  FROM compliance_records
);

